## Armstrong Principles

> "If you are worried about failure, write code that assumes things will fail, and make sure the system can recover." — Joe Armstrong

| Pillar | Principle | Key Rule |
|--------|-----------|----------|
| **Supervision** | Every worker has a supervisor | No orphan processes; documented restart strategy |
| **No Shared State** | Message passing only | No global mutex, no shared memory |
| **Let-It-Crash** | Fail fast, restart clean | No swallowed exceptions; crashes visible in logs |
| **Budget** | Every operation has limits | Time, memory, per-operation budgets enforced |

