## Armstrong Audit Checklist

### Supervision Tree
- [ ] Every worker process supervised (no orphans)
- [ ] Restart strategy documented per child (permanent/transient/temporary)
- [ ] max_restarts and max_seconds configured
- [ ] Crash in child does NOT crash parent
- [ ] Rapid restart count monitored

### No Shared State
- [ ] No global mutable state (static mut, global Mutex)
- [ ] All inter-process communication via messages
- [ ] State mutations are atomic (single operation per message)
- [ ] Database operations use transactions

### Let-It-Crash
- [ ] No bare try/catch swallowing errors
- [ ] Crashes visible in supervisor logs with stack trace
- [ ] No code path that logs error and continues with corrupt state
- [ ] Supervisor catches crash and restarts cleanly

### Budget Constraints
- [ ] Every operation has max_time_ms budget
- [ ] Timeout triggers escalation, not silent failure
- [ ] Memory limits configured and monitored
- [ ] Per-tier budgets defined (critical/high/normal/low)

